snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly, when I first looked at the title, I thought one of the issues was going to be about the purple hair dreadlocks because a couple of accounts that I followed on a couple of social media was making a big deal out of it and so did Twitter. Now, I'm not trying to invalidate anyone who has an issue with that and it's definitely not my place to say. I get it. I don't have this issue. So please don't start any fights with me.
But try to see from my perspective here, I think there are bigger issues than just hair and even though I don't know who Jeffree Star truly is when off-camera and despite the messed up things he did in the past (a decade ago), he has constantly apologized and for people to continue to hold him for his actions in the past (the stuff that happened more than a decade ago) is becoming/has become already pointless if he has already realized what he was doing and tried to make up for it to be truly a good person. Despite recent issues, that's a different story. It just seems like to me everyone is just picking something that they want to be mad about.


I don't know, that's just my opinion and how I feel. I follow Jeffree Star because I like his content and I honestly think he's an awesome makeup artist. If you feel differently and have different opinions, that's okay. I respect them.

It felt like they were both trying to convince us to buy Jeffree's pallete as well as promoting Mitchell's collabs, because Mitchell was using some of the products. The video makes sense with Mitchell putting makeup on Jeffree, but the title is quite misleading ... The video discussing the "purple issues" should have been a separate video with only Jefree.
For the record this is not putting out hate or trying to create drama, this is just simply my point of view and also my personal opinion on everything 🤷‍♀️😪
